This paper deals with graph games and their algorithms, which are primarily studied in the field of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) to solve the problem of mean payoff parity games. Additionally, the paper's relevance in synthesis of reactive systems suggests that it may also belong to the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper involves the use of mathematical logic and reasoning, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO).
